The official Global Citizen EP will be released this Friday, 30 November. Titled Global Citizen EP 1, the proceeds from the collaborative work will go towards supporting the advocacy organisation’s mission to end extreme poverty by 2030 and achieve the UN’s Sustainable Development Goals as well as its work in areas such as gender equality, education, water and sanitation. The four-track project will feature renowned musicians Pharrell Williams, Stormzy, Cassper Nyovest, Tiwa Savage, David Guetta, Wizkid Stargate, Los Unidades, Jozzy, Jess Kent, and Danny Ocean. The first single from the EP, E-Lo by Los Unidades and Pharrell Williams featuring Jozzy is already available for download and streaming. The song is accompanied by a Nelson Mandela inspired lyric video to mark what would have been the South African leader’s centenary year. The EP was spearheaded by Coldplay’s Chris Martin who is the curator of Global Citizen’s annual live music festivals. The full track-list of the EP is as follows: 1. Rise Up (feat. Nelson Mandela) – Stargate ?2. E-Lo (feat. Jozzy) – Los Unidades & Pharrell Williams? 3. Timbuktu (feat. Stormzy & Jess Kent) – Cassper Nyovest & Los Unidades? 4. Voodoo (feat. Tiwa Savage, Wizkid, Danny Ocean & David Guetta) – Stargate & Los Unidades The EP is available for pre-order here. Global Citizen Festival: Mandela 100 is presented and hosted by The Motsepe Foundation and will take place on December 2 at FNB Stadium in Johannesburg. On the bill to perform is Beyoncé, JAY-Z, Cassper Nyovest, D'banj, Ed Sheeran, Eddie Vedder, Femi Kuti, Pharrell Williams, Sho Madjozi, Tiwa Savage, Usher, Wizkid and Chris Martin.     